[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I knew it is not allowed to get the mutable reference to an object wrapped with Arc.<br>\nBut I need to get the mutable reference for below code.</p>\n<p>Below code is a Rust version of a example from Linux Device Drivers book chapter 06.<br>\nIt calls wait_for_completion in read system-call.<br>\nAnd it calls complete in write system-call.<br>\nThe completion object is inside of shared object wrapped with ArcBorrow.<br>\nTherefore both of read and write system-calls locks the inner structure inside of the shared object to get the mutable reference.</p>\n<p>That generates the dead-lock.</p>\n<p>Is there a another way to get the mutable reference to a filed in Arc?<br>\nOr could you please give me any tip to work-around that dead-lock problem?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">//! Rust LDD scull</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//! reference: https://github.com/d0u9/Linux-Device-Driver/tree/master/eg_03_scull_basic</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//!</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//! How to build only modules:</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//! make LLVM=1 M=samples/rust</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//!</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//! How to use:</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//! / # insmod rust_ldd06.ko</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//! / # mknod /dev/rust_ldd06 c 10 124</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//! / # cat /dev/rust_ldd06 &amp;</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">//! / # echo \"hello\" &gt; /dev/rust_ldd06</span>\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span>::<span class=\"n\">prelude</span>::<span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span>::<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c_str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">file</span>::<span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">File</span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">fmt</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">io_buffer</span>::<span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">IoBufferReader</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IoBufferWriter</span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">miscdev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">new_mutex</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">sync</span>::<span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">Arc</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mutex</span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span>: <span class=\"nc\">RustCompletion</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">name</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"rust_completion\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">author</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"Rust for Linux Contributors\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">description</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"Rust LDD ch06\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">license</span>: <span class=\"s\">\"GPL\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">// Fist I made CompletionDev { completion: bindings::completion }.</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// But it didn't work because we cannot get mutable reference to CompletionDev in read/write functions.</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// The argument of read/write functions is ArcBorrow&lt;'_, CompletionDev&gt;.</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// So it's not allowed to get the mutable reference to CompletionDev.</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// The only way to mutate through ArcBorrow is to use Mutex/RwLock/Atomic types.</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// (see doc.rust-lang.org/std/sync/struct.Mutex.html)</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// Finally I makde CompletionInner struct and put it into Mutex.</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">CompletionInner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">completion</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">// internal info between file operations</span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Mutex</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">CompletionInner</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">// TODO: impl CompletionDev::try_new</span>\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">try_new</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"completion_dev created</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">//</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// #define init_swait_queue_head(q)             \\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// do {                         \\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">//    static struct lock_class_key __key;       \\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">//    __init_swait_queue_head((q), #q, &amp;__key); \\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">//} while (0)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">completion</span>::<span class=\"n\">default</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compl_name</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c_str</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"completion_dev\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">key</span>: <span class=\"nc\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">lock_class_key</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">lock_class_key</span>::<span class=\"n\">default</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">compl</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">__init_swait_queue_head</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compl</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wait</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">compl_name</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_char_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">ffi</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_char</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Arc</span>::<span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pin_init</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">new_mutex</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">CompletionInner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">compl</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}))</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Sync</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Send</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">// unit struct for file operations</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">RustFile</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"cp\">#[vtable]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">file</span>::<span class=\"n\">Operations</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RustFile</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"nc\">Data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"nc\">OpenData</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">open</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">shared</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_file</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">file</span>::<span class=\"n\">File</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span>::<span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"open is invoked</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">,);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clone</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">//</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">read</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">shared</span>: <span class=\"nc\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">File</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">_data</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IoBufferWriter</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">_offset</span>: <span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"read is invoked</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inner_guard</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">lock</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">wait_for_completion</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inner_guard</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">completion</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">shared</span>: <span class=\"nc\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">File</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">data</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IoBufferReader</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">_offset</span>: <span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"write is invoked</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inner_guard</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">lock</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">complete</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inner_guard</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">completion</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// return non-zero value to avoid infinite re-try</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">release</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_data</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Self</span>::<span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_file</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">File</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"release is invoked</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">RustCompletion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_dev</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">miscdev</span>::<span class=\"n\">Registration</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">RustFile</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span>::<span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RustCompletion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_module</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"rust_ldd06 is loaded</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CompletionDev</span>::<span class=\"n\">try_new</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">reg</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">miscdev</span>::<span class=\"n\">Registration</span>::<span class=\"n\">new_pinned</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">fmt</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"rust_ldd06\"</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">RustCompletion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_dev</span>: <span class=\"nc\">reg</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Drop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RustCompletion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">drop</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">pr_info</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"rust_ldd06 is unloaded</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 399294094,
        "sender_full_name": "Gioh Kim",
        "timestamp": 1698670078
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"550518\">@Gioh Kim</span> ,<br>\nKernel completion implementation is internally synchronized, so you don't have to hold it inside a mutex. But I guess you did that because you needed a mut pointer when calling the C side functions.<br>\nMy recommendation will be is to rework the CompletionInner into something like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">Completion</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Opaque</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">completion</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Sync</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Completion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Send</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Completion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Completion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">new</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">       </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">completion</span>::<span class=\"n\">default</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">caller_lock_class</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">compl</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">done</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">__init_swait_queue_head</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compl</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wait</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_char_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Opaque</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">compl</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">wait_for_completion</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">wait_for_completion</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mf\">0.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">complete</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">complete</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mf\">0.</span><span class=\"n\">get</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>And this could be extracted in it's own module.</p>\n<p>And then in your <code>CompletionDev</code> you no longer need the <code>Mutex</code>.</p>\n<p>BTW, I didn't verify my snippet, but I hope you get the idea.</p>",
        "id": 399304116,
        "sender_full_name": "Razvan Heghedus",
        "timestamp": 1698673327
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>correct, but notice <code>Completion</code> should be pin-init</p>",
        "id": 399304242,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1698673364
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right. Forgot about that. I don't think we can have:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">Completion</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Opaque</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">completion</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but then the correct definition would be:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">Completion</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Opaque</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">completion</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>with the necessary adjustments to initialization and function calls.</p>",
        "id": 399306481,
        "sender_full_name": "Razvan Heghedus",
        "timestamp": 1698674061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I fixed it.<br>\nI used Opaque and Opaque::raw_get() to get the mutable pointer to the completion.<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/gurugio/rust-for-linux/commit/c038d5aef9f6ac97d6c5aa49b3bedc287377b883\">https://github.com/gurugio/rust-for-linux/commit/c038d5aef9f6ac97d6c5aa49b3bedc287377b883</a></p>\n<p>But it still has a problem.<br>\nI guess the completion object is not initialized correctly.<br>\nCould you please review that patch again?</p>\n<p>I’m really grateful for your help.</p>",
        "id": 399386662,
        "sender_full_name": "Gioh Kim",
        "timestamp": 1698705269
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You are initializing <code>compl</code> on the stack and then moving it into the final location. You should consider using <code>Opaque::ffi_init</code>.</p>",
        "id": 399387999,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1698706276
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I thought Opaque::new is like Box::new. I'll try it. Thank you very much.</p>",
        "id": 399412580,
        "sender_full_name": "Gioh Kim",
        "timestamp": 1698719449
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>how would <code>Box::new</code> change this? the initialization still happened on the stack and then gets moved to the heap. What you need to do is to initialize the struct directly on the heap. Feel free to post your code again :)</p>",
        "id": 399517899,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1698757761
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I guess what is different between \"allocate it on stack and move to heap\" and \"allocate it directly on heap\" is:<br>\n\"allocate it on stack and move to heap\" does</p>\n<ol>\n<li>allocate it on stack -&gt; pointer values are stack addresses</li>\n<li>moved to heap -&gt; pointer values are still stack addresses</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\"allocate it directly on heap\" does</p>\n<ol>\n<li>allocate it on heap</li>\n<li>all pointers are heap addresses</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Am I right?<br>\nIs there another reason?</p>\n<p>Nevertheless it's working now as below.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">insmod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">share</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust_ldd06</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ko</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">784.399060</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">rust_ldd06</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">loaded</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">784.400044</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">completion_dev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">created</span>\n<span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust_ldd06</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">785.944556</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">invoked</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">785.945798</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">read</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">invoked</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>#\n<span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">echo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"dd\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust_ldd06</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">788.842240</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">invoked</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">788.843574</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">write</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">invoked</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">788.844799</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">wait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">done</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">788.845910</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">release</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">invoked</span>\n<span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">788.847220</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_completion</span>: <span class=\"nc\">release</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">invoked</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>A full code: <a href=\"https://github.com/gurugio/rust-for-linux/blob/rust-next-ldd-ch06/samples/rust/rust_ldd06.rs\">https://github.com/gurugio/rust-for-linux/blob/rust-next-ldd-ch06/samples/rust/rust_ldd06.rs</a><br>\n(I copied a link to source file to make this short. I'll copy full code here if you prefer it rather than a link.)</p>\n<p>You made my day!<br>\nThank you very much!</p>",
        "id": 399544584,
        "sender_full_name": "Gioh Kim",
        "timestamp": 1698765803
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"550518\">Gioh Kim</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Getting.20mutable.20reference.20to.20Arc/near/399544584\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I guess what is different between \"allocate it on stack and move to heap\" and \"allocate it directly on heap\" is:<br>\n\"allocate it on stack and move to heap\" does</p>\n<ol>\n<li>allocate it on stack -&gt; pointer values are stack addresses</li>\n<li>moved to heap -&gt; pointer values are still stack addresses</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\"allocate it directly on heap\" does</p>\n<ol>\n<li>allocate it on heap</li>\n<li>all pointers are heap addresses</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Am I right?<br>\nIs there another reason?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, that's right.</p>",
